@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container-fluid my-2 privacy-section">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 offset-md-2">
            <h1 class="text-center mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

            <p class="mb-4">We take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect your information.</p>

            <h3>Information Collection and Use</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">We may collect personal information, such as your name, email address, and contact details, when you register an account, subscribe to our newsletter, or fill out a form on our website. This information is voluntarily provided by you and will be used by CUT to assist you by sharing further information and/or respond to an enquiry. Opting not to share personal information may result in CUT being unable to provide the required service and/or information.</p>

            <h3>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties without your consent, except as required by law or as necessary to provide our services. CUT adheres to the Electronic Communications and Transactions Act 25 of 2002, and the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPI Act).</p>

            <h3>Security</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">We implement security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

            <h3>Cookies</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">We use cookies to improve your experience on our website. You can choose to accept or decline cookies through your browser settings. Please note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality of certain parts of our website.</p>

            <h3>Communication</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Central University of Technology, Free State may use the personal information about the user to communicate with the user from time to time. Users may indicate if they do not wish to receive such communications; Furthermore, information will be processed according to its category (stakeholders groups).</p>

            <h3>Complaints and Enquiries</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">To lodge a complaint or enquire about personal information use, contact the CUT Registrar’s Office at <a href="mailto:registrar@cut.ac.za">registrar@cut.ac.za</a> or in writing: The Registrar, Central University of Technology, Free State Private Bag X20539, BLOEMFONTEIN, 9300, Republic of South Africa.</p>

            <p class="text-muted">Last Updated: April 2024</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    
</div>

<style>
    .privacy-section {
        background-image: url('/assets/data-privacy_icon.pgn');
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-position: center center;
        background-size: 120px; 
        padding-top: 60px; 
        position: relative;
    }

    .privacy-section::after {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        background-color: rgba(0, 148, 255, 0.1); 
    }
</style>
